  "prompt": "What's a good uninstalled for windows?",
  "response": "There are several good uninstallers available for Windows that help remove applications more thoroughly than the built-in uninstaller. Some of the popular ones include:\n\n1. **Revo Uninstaller**: This is one of the most well-known uninstallers, offering a robust set of features including advanced scanning for leftover files, folders, and registry entries. Revo offers both free and paid versions.\n\n2. **IObit Uninstaller**: Known for its user-friendly interface, IObit Uninstaller provides a powerful scan engine to remove stubborn programs and browser plug-ins. It also includes additional features such as software updater and browser toolbar removal.\n\n3. **Geek Uninstaller**: This is a lightweight and portable uninstaller that's easy to use, providing a simple interface and efficient removal of residual files and registry entries.\n\n4. **Bulk Crap Uninstaller (BCUninstaller)**: A free tool aimed at more advanced users, BCUninstaller is highly effective, particularly for removing a large number of programs at once. It provides detailed information and allows for batch processing.\n\n5. **Ashampoo UnInstaller**: This program not only uninstalls applications but also monitors installations to ensure a clean removal process. It includes various additional tools for system maintenance.\n\nWhen choosing an uninstaller, consider factors such as ease of use, additional features, and whether they fit your specific needs (e.g., free vs. paid, additional cleanup capabilities).",
